ion of individual liberties on the one hand, and the simultaneous establishment of new control mechanisms on the other. The work of the early German Franciscans presented here exemplifies the dialectics of social diversification processes that shaped Europe in the Middle Ages and later.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aMonasticism and religious orderszGermanyxHistory. 4aBettelorden. 4aFranziskaner. 4aKirchengeschichte. 4aSozialer Wandel. 4aZivilisationsprozess. 7aRELIGION / Christian Theology / History.2bisacsh  aFranciscans.  aMendicant order.  achurch history.  aprocess of civilization.  asocial change.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2008z9783110209280oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311018544740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311020081240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110200812423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110200812/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014